  "texts": [
    "Characteristics of a biological agent, such as a pathogen or toxin or one of its subcomponents, which can directly enhance its harmful potential.",
    "These include factors such as immune modulation, host and tissue tropism, replication rate, receptor binding specificity, membrane disruption, potency, avidity, solubility and other attributes that influence pathogenicity or detectability.",
    "These terms refer to the extent to which the changes make the agent more harmful or weaponisable.",
    "The change required will vary with the agent and is a subjective assessment.",
    "Refers to any modification that has not been previously documented, and leads to a non-trivial functional change."
  ],
